cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with depth estimation from images. The use of deep learning and adversarial training suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The fact that the proposed approach is specifically designed for binocular stereo depth estimation suggests that it could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of unsupervised learning suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
